<p>I have a simple rails app where i have divided users into roles <strong>Sellers</strong> and <strong>Customers</strong> with id 1 and 2 respectively. Now i want <strong>customers</strong> to see something different then <strong>sellers</strong> on the index page and for that I had tried this but nothing happened.</p>  <pre><code>        &lt;div class="container-fluid"&gt;     &lt;div class="col-md-12 text-right"&gt;         &lt;% if role_id == 1 %&gt;             &lt;%= link_to "Add a new Shipment", new_shipment_path, class: "btn btn-success" %&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;         &lt;% else %&gt;             &lt;% @shipments.each do |shipment| %&gt;         &lt;div class="shipment"&gt;         &lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;%= shipment.user.full_name%&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;         &lt;h5&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DESCRIPTION: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;%= shipment.description %&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;          &lt;div class="thumbnail"&gt;         &lt;td&gt;&lt;%= image_tag shipment.image.url(:medium)%&gt;&lt;/td&gt;           &lt;div class="meta"&gt;             &lt;%= link_to time_ago_in_words(shipment.created_at) + " ago" %&gt; |             &lt;%= link_to "show", shipment %&gt;             &lt;span class="admin"&gt;                | &lt;%= link_to "Edit", edit_shipment_path(shipment) %&gt; |               &lt;%= link_to "Delete", shipment, method: :delete, data: { confirm: "Hey! Are you sure! You wanna delete this shipment??"} %&gt;           &lt;/span&gt;             &lt;/div&gt;           &lt;/div&gt;           &lt;% end %&gt;         &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;         &lt;% end %&gt; </code></pre>  <p><em>My seeds.rb</em></p>  <pre><code>['seller', 'customer'].each do |role|   Role.find_or_create_by({name: role}) end </code></pre>